    "body": "Superseded by #11981 .\r\nAlternative to #7862.\r\n\r\nThis approach allows for the definition of no-source -- or bundle -- packages that contain no source (or code) of their own to install; rather, they are used to encapsulate a set of dependencies.\r\n\r\nTODO:\r\n- [x] Rename `DependenciesPackage` to `BundlePackage` (see #7862)\r\n- [x] Re-run `xsdk`\r\n- [x] Add unit tests\r\n- [x]  Fix `spack info` (and ensure it \"works\" for `BundlePackage`s (e.g., `xsdk`)\r\n\r\nUPDATE:\r\n- Alternative approach with minimal impact on `Package` with `BundlePackage`-related changes in/moved to PR #11981\r\n- Basic template tests -- not of `BundlePackage` -- moved to separate PR #11970 \r\n- `uninstall_by_spec` error tests moved to separate PR #11971 \r\n- Extra `possible_dependencies` checks (for coverage) moved to separate PR #11988 ",
